  "text": "At the end of the experiments, both lungs of the studied animals, excluding their hilar structures, were excised and immediately weighed. Thereafter, lungs were dried in an oven at 100°C overnight and then re-weighted. Lung wet/dry weight ratios were calculated by dividing the wet weight by the dry weight as described previously [CITATION_1] .",
